I have been going through old recipes of mine, and found this one printed from years ago tucked away in my cabinet between a cold carrot soup and risotto recipe. It's funny how you remember the recipe when it is put in context of others you were making at the time. Anyway, I re- read my notes that I jotted down on the paper and here they are: this was really good, even if it required a little more prep than I like for a simple salad. I said "worth it". I remember, too, being disappointed that my pears were bruised, as their symmetry and flawlessness are somewhat integral to the presentation of the salad. No one wants to have a lovely spread of greens and bright cheese and toasted nuts next to a fan of pears that look like they were thrown around the kitchen first. Anyway - this was lovely, and I would make it for entertaining more than I would for just my boyfriend and myself. I made it early on in our "dating career" when impressing him with my culinary prowess in the kitchen was more important to me than getting something on the table quickly... Now, he'll have to settle for seeing this pretty dish if we have friends come over :)

