Beautiful presentation. Used the cider vinegar and frozen white grape juice concentrate (did not dilute)for a lovely light dressing. 15 minutes was just right as long as the pears are not too ripe. Used slices of maytag blue. Guests loved his dish. Cutting the pears at an angle was a great tip.

Rating: 4
This is editted to add from my previous review... A note on cutting the pears: To get the pears to fan out beautifully, cut them on a slight angle when you are making your slits. If you cut with your knife perpendicular to the cutting board, you will not be able to fan the slices well. Good luck and enjoy!

