Rating: 4
Wow! What an outstanding and unusual combination of flavors, with great visual appeal .. and easy to boot! I made this for my husband and I on a whim tonight and made several substitutions based on what I had on hand: I used Bosc pears rather than Bartlett, dried thyme rather than fresh (simply sprinkling it on the baking sheet before placing the pears on it), purple grape juice rather than white, toasted walnuts instead of toasted hazelnuts, and baby spinach rather than arugula. I used slices of Saga Blue. I also added just a smidgen of honey to the salad dressing. Obviously, the recipe is very flexible, because this was terrific!! One of the best salads I've made. I can't wait to serve it to guests! Very, very impressive. I'll be making this often.

