This salad is wonderful and has quickly become a favorite. The combination of greens, fruit, nut and cheese in a salad always gets my attention -- and the toasted hazelnuts are a nice "regional" touch here in Oregon. It took me a few tries to get the hang of cutting the pears just right, but the gorgeous visual presentation is worth it. I use the dressing sparingly as I personally prefer a lighter coverage, but the flavor is sublime. This salad would lend itself to some variations -- for example, I've used "cousin" cheeses with good effect, including Gorgonzola and Stilton.

